@LBA2_PRODUCT_NAME@ @LBA2_VERSION_STRING@
====================================================

@LBA2_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION@

This is a portable build. No installer, no registry entries. Drop
@LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe wherever you want and run.


GAME DATA
---------

This fork doesn't include game data — you need a legitimate copy of
Little Big Adventure 2 / Twinsen's Odyssey from GOG, Steam, or your
original retail CD.

Easiest setup: just double-click @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe. A folder
picker will open and ask you to point at your retail install — the
folder containing lba2.hqr (alongside music\, video\, vox\, etc., or
under a Common\ or CommonClassic\ subfolder for Steam/GOG re-releases).
Your choice is remembered, so subsequent launches skip the picker.

Alternative — drop @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe directly into your
existing LBA2 install folder and run it from there. The engine
auto-discovers game data in the directory the .exe is launched from
(or in a "data" / "game" subfolder next to it), so the picker won't
appear in that case.

To re-pick later (e.g. switching between two installs):

    @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe --pick-game-dir

Or skip the picker entirely with an explicit path:

    @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe --game-dir "C:\path\to\game"
    set LBA2_GAME_DIR=C:\path\to\game

The remembered choice lives at:

    %APPDATA%\Twinsen\LBA2\last_game_dir.txt

Delete it to force the picker to re-appear on next launch.


RUNNING
-------

Double-click @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe, or run from cmd.exe /
PowerShell. If it can't find game data and the picker isn't available
for some reason, the log file in your user profile lists every
directory it tried.


